l9bbXUdC9v0-: The food and service are top notch here. You are greeted by a friendly and professional staff as you walk into the restaurant. I think i've eaten everything on the menu. Sundays they have Tacos Al Pastor. I found a happy hour, to my surprise (M-F), last night. If you bring children there is a safe and well thought out area for the children to play. Parents have a full view of the area so they may keep an eye on their children and allow them the freedom to play. The meat grilled tacos are excellent, as is the Al Pastor tacos. l9bbXUdC9v0-: First the map directions are completely wrong. The directions sent us to the Hilton. We called the restaurant and got correct directions, 14km away! It was well worth the drive. The service was excellent, friendly and efficient. We shared many dishes and all of them were super. The ones that stood out were the Tuna Tirado, the Peruvian Ceviche and the Dirty Rice with egg. I have lived in Peru many years, I got very fond of the Ceviche and for sure this was the nearest to the Ceviche that I was used too in Lima.

I took my wife and Motherinlaw out for her brithday. We celebrated and tried many of the appetizers, entrees, and desserts. Obviously we didnt finish most of them.
